  "prompt": "What is the oldest book ever written?",
  "response": "The title of the \"oldest book ever written\" can vary depending on how one defines a book. If we consider the oldest known written text, that would be the \"Epic of Gilgamesh,\" which dates back to around 2100 BCE in ancient Mesopotamia. It was inscribed on clay tablets and is one of the earliest works of literary fiction.\n\nIf you are referring to the oldest surviving bound book, \"The Diamond Sutra,\" a Chinese text printed in 868 CE, holds that distinction. It is the oldest known complete printed book.\n\nEach of these examples serves as a representation of early human writing and literature, but the concept of a \"book\" can encompass a variety of formats and definitions.",
